:: Rejection target: the reduction duplicates the pattern variable `x` on the
:: right-hand side (one free occurrence in the LHS, two in the RHS) even though
:: the node count still shrinks. Spec 17.6.4 rule 2 requires per-variable free
:: occurrence counts in the RHS to stay within the LHS counts, keeping the
:: order substitution-stable
:: (doc/spec/en/17.clusters_and_registrations.md, section 17.6.4, rule 2).

definition
  let x, y be set;
  func JoinDef: join(x, y) -> set equals x;
  func PackDef: pack(x, y) -> set equals [x];
end;

registration
  let x, y be set;

  reduce PackDup: pack(join(x, y), y) to join(x, x);
  reducibility proof thus thesis; end;
end;
